{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"tricolour-head-ratfish","description":"# Compaction: rename folded events to `*.retired` (implement invariant I1)\n\nReplace compaction's hard delete of folded event files with a rename to `*.retired`, so a\ndelete/add reconciliation (e.g. a rebase, RC1-class) can never resurrect a folded source event.\nImplements the behavior `docs/concurrency.md` invariant I1 already documents but the code does not.\nPrerequisite for A2's rebuild backstop and A3's remediation.\n\n## What / files\n- `src/rebar/_commands/compact.py:140-144` — replace `os.remove(fp)` with rename -> `<name>.retired`.\n- `src/rebar/reducer/_cache.py` — confirm the `*.json` glob excludes `*.retired` (folded files leave replay).\n- `src/rebar/_commands/fsck.py` — confirm `.retired` is skipped; `SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT` must not fire on a retired-but-present source file.\n- `docs/concurrency.md` (I1) — align doc <-> code.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Folded source files are renamed to `*.retired`, never `os.remove`d.\n- [ ] Retired files are excluded from reducer replay and from fsck loops.\n- [ ] `SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT` no longer fires when a folded file was retired (not deleted).\n- [ ] Two-clone merge+rebase resurrection regression test: RED before, GREEN after.\n- [ ] `docs/concurrency.md` I1 and the compaction code agree.\n","id":"b306-d68c-8ded-4bff","parent_id":"ace2-f784-4b19-4f22","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Compaction: non-destructive `*.retired` rename (invariant I1)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783470411577536001,"uuid":"561a8a6d-54a7-4286-a253-8211ff5d7a4c"}